pOr6IEz5QwAXQKK7hsDQjQ.text: Came here only because I was staying at the hotel next door and it was pouring in London. Food is pretty good but it takes forever! Should have ventured out in the rain since I waited over 30mins for an appetizer and an additional 25min for the entree.

Al4uUSyTBFtxtWuQa2cHLw.text: Food here was good and service was fine too.  Our only complaint on service was that we had to flag down our server to bring the check.We had the bread service, a chorizo burger, mushroom soup and scampi popcorn which is little bits of fried fish kind of like a chicken nugget but seafood.  Sauce was good.  Mushroom soup was not bad but just wasn't what I expected.  Normally we put cream in a mushroom soup but this one was just water and finely chopped up mushrooms with a sprig of thyme.  Again, wasn't bad just not what I expected and somewhat bland.  Good for outdoor dining.

LADS8L3wf6U0flMeFvR96Q.text: Came here for a lunch meal. As we started ordering we were told that the kitchen was very busy and we may have a delay in getting the food. Not a good start. We decided to plough on. We ordered mains & thought we'd get some bread & olives to nibble on while we waited for the mains. It took 20mins to cut the bread & spoon the olives into a bowl. We got the mains not long after. Food was ok. Not really worth it though.

PoCLH3-wZtwPBJbeUbffCw.text: The first time I went here it was a 5 star bonus surprise.Last time wasn't so good, but it still deserved 4 stars.Right now I've been sitting here for 26 minutes. It took over 15 minutes for someone to come and ask if I want a drink. 11 minutes later I had to ask one of the waiters what's going on. This is completely unacceptable as they aren't even that busy. So I'm dropping it to 2 stars.It's rather annoying that they stop serving brunch (breakfast) at 11.30am. This has thwarted me before as its become the norm in London to have a brunch past midday at most of the usual quality brunch spots.But then, they do call it breakfast here, which is correct and traditional but not in keeping with the 21st century :)On to the food then.What can I say? Everything is delicious. The only reason I am dropping a star is that I can't have it when I want to have it! The atmosphere is lovely; light and airy with high ceilings and a feeling of space. Terrible service is letting this place down. Sort it out guys!

IeY8V0z6c_KKh-7yhDfWKg.text: Love the lighting and decor of the restaurant. The waitress was very attentive and the chef was accommodating to certain dietary restrictions. The food was wonderful and exceed my very high standards and expectations. The smoothies are also really good so if give those a try!

MqYqWw4aQPMZEhCuLXfIVA.text: I immediately loved the decor. Lots of wood and glass.  Think gastropub meets Starbucks.  The food was fresh, thoughtful, and well-prepared.  Unfortunately, it lost a star from me due to slow service.

VOOmV1fdnCxzMyNm-prQXA.text: The food here is excellent, but the service and speed of service is horrible.  Don't come here unless you have a lot of time.  I have eaten here four times in the past 6 months.  The hummus falafel starter is good,  the caprese salad starter is very good.  The deserts are good.  Today I had the sea bass special and it was excellent.  I would give 5 stars for the food and 1 for the service,  so that averages out to 3 stars.  If they would just hire staff that pays more attention I would easily give 5 stars.  Every single time I have eaten here I had to flag someone down to bring the check,  and this was after waiting a very long time for someone to bring it.

photos.caption: Photo of Natural Kitchen - London, United Kingdom. This was the sea bass special. It was excellent.

Hvwh-2qlptqoOnRs-tp9Gg.text: The Friday Night Special at Natural Kitchen's Trinity Square is Fish and Chips. While as much a staple to UK fare as hamburgers are to us in the US, as a regular traveler to London, I have had my share of the epicurean comfort food and this presentation and the taste were massive. An absolutely brilliant  meal. As the picture shows, the piece of cod was huge (not a single bone to have to deal with), and placed on top of the hand-cut, homemade chips. A separate dish of mushy peas accompanied the meal, along with perhaps the best made from scratch (I asked) tartar sauce I have ever had.Service was very attentive and unlike some other places, the server actually spoke and understood English! Ask for Eva. She was really great. The entree came out quickly, but we were not rushed and enjoyed an outstanding meal. No good meal is complete without a proper sweet or pudding at the end. Natural Kitchen had several from which to choose. I had a plain dish of strawberry and vanilla ice cream...with the emphasis being on the "creamy." Delicious and a generous portion. Enjoyed the experience and food quality so much that I am heading back tomorrow night with 3 businesss colleagues over from the states.

photos.caption: Photo of Natural Kitchen - London, United Kingdom. The Friday Night Fish and Chips special at Natural Kitchen Trinity Square. Somethimes pictures are worth a thousand words!

llnhDT10X2YUpJmwyu9nwA.text: Unbelievable value and delicious food.  The food is organic and fresh.  I had the Tuna Steak and it was done to perfection. I'm not easy to please when it comes to food, but I was completely satisfied.  My wife has the risotto and absolutely enjoyed it.

photos.caption: Photo of Natural Kitchen - London, United Kingdom. Yum Tuna Steak.

WxB1ajE3VsfTXEGPei72-Q.text: Good spot for a quick nutritious meal or snack but a bit pricey compared to other options in the area. The happy hour specials are great, though, so stop by after work for a tasty Mojito at only £5. The outdoor seating area is also quite nice and robust - perfect spot to meet a few colleagues after work.

1K4xqOSpwAGCGSMMV7jFnw.text: The food is not bad but I am being subjected to ludicrously bad treatment. I ordered my food literally 50 minutes ago. The waiters are consistently making the wait worse: they keep explaining that there is a big table that is taking precedence over my order. It doesn't get worse than that!

gVq_eovoReX6zPzs8Xmatg.text: Great evening meal, nice location, good ambiance and great service. Good portions very fresh vegetables great range of burgers

oZ2sT-9J4QlcxaWl80fW4g.text: the space looks great, the decoration is top notch. after that, fine print on menu is really, really hard to read. the seevice is really not get there, wait for 15 minutes for ordered water and waitress even not bother to apologize. first time and last time at natural kitchen

A_94hnZSiKjN4TGi5T_aFQ.text: Absolutely terrible service. Lady next to me ordered a hamburger along with her son and never got her order. I received my starter but waited 40min before someone stopped to ask me, are you still waiting for your food"? Good food but have to say the service is appallingly bad.

NkuqAx5YgiMeZ3OESqzgoA.text: Really great food here- healthy & fresh! I had salmon and steamed veggies- my daughter had asparagus risotto and we both had delicious tarts for dessert- lemon & chocolate. Also a nice moderately priced bottle of Rose. I was here 2 years ago and also had a great experience.

qB16KgoMTf0OfOYyfRUKAw.text: Got the line caught tuna salad.  Was really tasty.  Sometimes it's hard to get " healthy food" with so much fish and chips about so this was nice.  Flourless chocolate cake was good too.  This place is pricy but what isn't in this area.  Four stars for London.  Three stars if this was in Chicago or San Fran

h-VDxbCJuNiWPjmiwVGooQ.text: Small rock in our salad.  Staff shrugged shoulders about it when informed. I was little surprised by the lack of response.

ARZuYIjAEAJl0Rfn8nNEwQ.text: Breakfast was great.  Had good latte, ham and cheese croissant (flaky and yummy ), yogurt with fruit and granola, good prices.

7DUtZSYuGD8rvylDFg4LuA.text: Ok first let me say this is an American reviewing a London eating establishment so take this with a grain of salt... Located in the Double Tree by Hilton right near the tower this is a pretty good choice for a lite meal.The chicken bites from the appetizer menu are very good and a small portion is just right for quick snack.The best choice from the appetizer menu is the Hummus with pita.  Very well crafted, presentation was great and flavorful beyond what I expected!They do add a gratuity to every bill which is listed on the menu in very small print so keep that in mind when you tip.

photos.caption: Photo of Natural Kitchen - London, United Kingdom. Chicken bites were very good
Photo of Natural Kitchen - London, United Kingdom. Hummus from appetizer side of menu stole the show!

Z0d0NvrgoGsq_dTKFUgJ3w.text: Adjoining restaurant to the DoubleTree Tower of London offering a variety of fresh and craft entrees with a small but nice selection of drafts on tap.Outdoor patio seating with rustic feel is an extension of the indoor dining area.  Weather was lovely so it was great sitting outdoor, lounging and enjoying our meal. Staff was attentive, friendly and courteous. Prices are moderate which equaled the portion sizes of the plates.  Hummus appetizer and burgers were the meal of choice and they did not disappoint.

photos.caption: Photo of Natural Kitchen - London, United Kingdom. Appetizer Hummus and Flatbread. Delicious!!

TgJG4hc3BZw0sbKJkj23uw.text: I love their message and their menu! AllAbout healthy and wholesome foods that taste good and nourish your activities. We had the soupOf the day, chicken noodle. The bread was amazing and the soup was full ofFlavors.

B65R8SeEcb0fptKgJ2C1-Q.text: Good but not great food. Hideous service. Been waiting for my check for well over 30 minutes after they took my plates. Took my water bottle at least 25 minutes ago and have been ignored since. We Am going to complain at the front seat but I'm not even sure it's connected to the restaurant. It's not even busy.

8qtdDc5G66X6Vtwuj6Gobg.text: Food was delish and filling, and the selection was great for any dietary need.  Service was mediocre at best as we found ourselves waiting longer than necessary and having to flag down our person multiple times.

_vLeZClzmlq_IH56zDorTQ.text: Here for the third time in 2 days! The ingredients are organic and clean. The staff is amazing especially the manager who is very attentive to my particular dietary restrictive needs! Had a The Crunchy Raw Detox salad, sirloin steak, and switched out the tuna salad for the sea bass. All yummy and clean tasting! I'm so glad I found this place! Coming from New York I was concerned I wouldn't be able to find food places to meet my needs. Bonuses: close to attractions, choice of outdoor and indoor seating and the place looks super simple and clean decor wise.

o3KHqS5Nlw-2LYuZgJuYiQ.text: Wow-right around the corner from our hotel- this restaurant serves amazing real food! Would definitely go back- there were many things on the menu I would have loved to try! I had the grilled salmon salad and it was PERFECT!

IZVRgX678Kw6Tk50BniDbg.text: Lived in a hotel in the city for a week and came here almost every day for a meal. Their ingredients were fresh and all the dishes were nothing short of delicious and very healthy. They have an amazing selection of Organic and vegan wine (yes that's a thing!) And each dish is beautifully presented. Every time I am in the area I would come back here and highly recommend it to anyone in the area looking for a nice and healthy meal. The ambience is also very sweet, and the servers for the most part were very helpful and knowledgeable.

Lr1Pn1LC1tw2cqPyqdFg7Q.text: Great food that runs the gamut from vegan to steaks.  Everything was fresh and well prepared.  The fish and chips were really good with a full fish filet.  The tuna salad was very nicely done rare.  The mushroom soup was extraordinary.  A very nice moderately priced, for London.  Service was good, not great.  Noise level was loud as it is a large room with a very busy lunch service.  Overall a really nice lunch.

Z3i7CwAr6noFz7dAp7ys9w.text: This restaurant is located in the Double Tree Hotel. I'm not a fan of hotel restaurant but this one is different. Staff is friendly and the place is clean and relaxed. We sat outside and ordered fish and chips, soup of the day... mushroom soup...yum. Hubby had a salmon burger which he enjoyed. Elderflower bubbly drink is light and refreshing on warm days. We loved it and would definitely recommend.

1_-1vdki0to3oRs-29AS7g.text: Super slow and inattentive. Lots of items on menu 'not available. Forced payment before we'd finished our Luke warm food. Major disappointment

M0v5b8knP4gDGbfKVolyCA.text: I've tried several menu items and all were great. With Vegan, plant based, and non-dairy options - a rarity outside the U.S. - but this Cali girl was pleasantly surprised. Protein options range from steak, chicken and fish. They also have an organic wine list that's very tasty. Open late till about 10pm and the service is really good. In the morning I tried their detox smoothies and almond milk cappuccino. You can't go wrong!

dg4ENCIFGaiBVr2A3uTPJw.text: After last night's dinner I was in search of something more nutrient dense tonight.This is a gorgeous space with extremely high ceilings. For dinner I ordered a full days servings of fruit and vegetables. ;)Antitox smoothie, without the banana - you know the feeling you get when you are eating something really good for you that also tastes good? Excellent.Chicken breast burger, which came with tarragon coleslaw and sweet potato fries. The sandwich was huge and the fries were nicely baked. I ate half and was very happy with that.Peppermint tea Apple and berry crumble OMG delicious. More berry than apple, almonds in the crumble. Also huge.Pleasant prompt service, clean. Gem.

vkU0kNjJo2ndVZrvQFbF_g.text: Great place in a somewhat off off street.Friendly service, honest " british" food, good beers and wines, reasonable prices.If you are in the neighbourhood:worth the detour

ecm8sYip_KGfKQx-O1xRcg.text: This restaurant is fantastic! We stayed across the street, but stumbled upon this restaurant while looking for something healthy that might even work with our food allergies. First, the ambience is just great...glass windows to the vaulted ceiling, farmhouse style tables, very, very clean, and part of the restaurant is more for popping in and working cafe style. Second, the food is excellent, and since we ended up eating there for breakfast and our evening meal 4 times in all, we experienced quite a selection. Third, the entire staff was accommodating, friendly, and extremely professional and gracious. Raman (hope I'm not butchering the spelling) was above and beyond on our service, as well as being extremely thorough in regard to making sure the food was allergy safe, and even went the extra mile to look up and disclose the ingredients in our food. The juice bar creations were awesome to boot! I couldn't give this place more stars or I would! Go there! Your belly and tastebuds will thank you. Oh! If you happen to read a bad review from a grumpy, miserable old wretch of a human being, please don't pay it any mind. The woman two tables over in our last night was unbelievably rude to all the staff, and her complaints were not valid...bickering that she ordered a one shot latte and going through the roof insisting, with almost vulgar language, that it was not made properly and when she sat down she immediately started complaining about the food from her prior visit not being satisfactory  (which leads one to wonder why she returned on the first place). She was so horrible that the table seated next to her asked to be moved after having to listen to her horribleness at close range. Incidentally, while I would have asked the woman to leave, Raman handled allllll of her unsubstantiated complaints with grace and aplomb. Slow clap for the patient staff at Natural Kitchen. :)

oZ93FfI12ew49B-31r3KRA.text: We stumbled upon this place and since we appreciate fresh organic food we decided to try it. I ordered the chicken linguine with pesto sauce, had baby tomatoes and spinach mixed in- outstanding! my daughter ordered the salad with pancetta chicken rosemary croutons and Caesar dressing / also very good! We would def recommend this place and look forward to coming back again.

s854D-x1ZpC0UEAeRIQ2Fw.text: Gorgeous little restaurant: big floor to ceiling glass windows looking out onto cherry blossoms (I think) in full bloom. Everything else is clean wood and the little box bouquet of fresh herbs on each table is a nice touch.I got the crab & crayfish linguine based on a solid recommendation, and it was all kinds of tasty, albeit it's like walking into a wall of cream. Two of us who got the dish asked for a lemon wedge to cut back the acid, but fans of cheesy creamy comfort food would love this.

sWa-ONKzKA-ob2bOHEwYCw.text: Eating lunch and the place smells so good.  I came in for soup and I can't help but want to order more.  Do not come here when you are hungry...everything smells delicious!Food is delicious and love the environment.  Would be great for a casual dinner or a nice coffee.
